= <span style="color: #e49c21;">**LAPT**</span> Founding Congress

After a period of paralysis and indecision, [? if not lapt_r : unfortunately coinciding with the elections, ?] the white-collar unions have finally backed the <span style="color: #e49c21;">**LAPT**</span> and to that effect send their delegates to its founding congress, which will draft a proper party platform and ratify a proper leadership. 

Aspelund has spent this period somewhat radicalizing, looking to Caterino's Refugia as an inspiration and convinced in the necessity of a strong <span style="color: #d4130c;">Social</span><span style="color: #e49c21;">-</span><span style="color: #f5e324;">Republican</span> front to dismantle reaction and cement a cross-class social republic. It is uncertain if these ideas will resonate with the white-collar unions, or if they will trend towards a less radical-republican committment to corporatism.

