Fredrik Aspelund is, of course, the natural leader of this party, and he retains his clout from his former Minister-Presidency, and so his chairmanship of the party is confirmed by majority vote. However, the white-collar unions present amend his proposed radical-republican platform, ensuring that the <span style="color: #e49c21;">**LAPT**</span>'s support of a republic is simply an aspect of, rather than the crux, of the party's agenda.

Lukas Westergaard, the mind behind the party's formation, has been elected as co-leader.